※※
# rename-sky-workflow

Manually-run workflow that renames a `.sky` file atomically: it `git mv`s the file,
fixes its `⊕meta⊕ name =` field, and rewrites `sky run <old>` references across the
library — behind a manual gate — then lints the result and verifies the old name is
gone. Pure bash, no LLM tokens.

  (manual run: --var dir, name, new-name)
       │
       ▼
   ┌────────┐  not found ──▶ list <dir> + stop
   │  find  │  shows old->new + `sky run <old>` ref hits
   └────────┘
       │ found
       ▼
   ┌─────────┐  reject ──▶ stop (nothing changed)
   │ confirm │  ⏸ manual approval gate (timeout 1h)
   └─────────┘
       │ approve
       ▼
   ┌────────┐  git mv + fix name= + rewrite `sky run <old>`
   │ apply  │
   └────────┘
       │
       ▼
   ┌────────┐  sky lint new file; warn on leftover old refs
   │ verify │
   └────────┘
       │
       ▼
     done

Run it (state where the workflow lives with --var dir):

  sky run rename-sky-workflow \
    --var dir=".sky/workflows" \
    --var name="old-name" \
    --var new-name="new-name"

  - dir       directory the workflow lives in — STATE THIS (e.g. .sky/workflows)
  - name      current kebab-case filename (no .sky extension)
  - new-name  new kebab-case filename + workflow name (no .sky extension)

Scope note: the reference rewrite targets `sky run <old>` occurrences. It does a
plain text replace, so if one workflow name is a prefix of another the verify step
flags any leftover for manual review. It does not touch `sky_event` names (those are
event identifiers, not workflow names).
※※

⊕meta⊕
name = "rename-sky-workflow"
description = "Atomically rename a .sky: git mv, fix its meta name, rewrite `sky run <old>` refs behind a manual gate, then lint and verify. Fire via: sky run rename-sky-workflow --var dir=<dir> --var name=<old> --var new-name=<new>"
trigger.manual = true
output_style = "terse"
⊕⊕

※※
Step 1 — find. Resolves the source file, refuses if the target name already exists,
and prints every `sky run <old>` reference that the apply step will rewrite.
※※

§find§
bash = "OLD=\"$SKY_DIR/$SKY_NAME.sky\"\nNEW=\"$SKY_DIR/$SKY_NEW_NAME.sky\"\nif [ ! -f \"$OLD\" ]; then echo \"[rename] no workflow at $OLD\"; echo \"[rename] available in $SKY_DIR:\"; ls \"$SKY_DIR\" 2>/dev/null || true; exit 1; fi\nif [ -e \"$NEW\" ]; then echo \"[rename] target already exists: $NEW\"; exit 1; fi\necho \"[rename] $SKY_NAME -> $SKY_NEW_NAME\"\necho \"[rename] 'sky run $SKY_NAME' references in $SKY_DIR:\"\ngrep -rn \"sky run $SKY_NAME\" \"$SKY_DIR\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"  (none)\""
§§

※※
Step 2 — confirm. Manual gate. Rename + cross-file rewrite is disruptive, so a human
approves first. Reject to stop with nothing changed; timeout after 1h.
※※

§confirm§
depends_on = ["find"]
wait.prompt = "Rename {{name}} -> {{new-name}} in {{dir}} and rewrite `sky run {{name}}` references? Approve to apply."
wait.channel = "manual"
wait.timeout = "1h"
§§

※※
Step 3 — apply. git mv the file (falls back to mv if not a git repo), rewrite the
`name =` field in the moved file, then text-replace `sky run <old>` -> `sky run <new>`
across every .sky in the dir. Uses temp-file sed (portable on macOS + Linux).
※※

§apply§
depends_on = ["confirm"]
bash = "set -e\nOLD=\"$SKY_DIR/$SKY_NAME.sky\"\nNEW=\"$SKY_DIR/$SKY_NEW_NAME.sky\"\ngit mv \"$OLD\" \"$NEW\" 2>/dev/null || mv \"$OLD\" \"$NEW\"\nsed \"s/^name = \\\"$SKY_NAME\\\"/name = \\\"$SKY_NEW_NAME\\\"/\" \"$NEW\" > \"$NEW.tmp\" && mv \"$NEW.tmp\" \"$NEW\"\nfor f in \"$SKY_DIR\"/*.sky; do\n  [ -e \"$f\" ] || continue\n  sed \"s|sky run $SKY_NAME|sky run $SKY_NEW_NAME|g\" \"$f\" > \"$f.tmp\" && mv \"$f.tmp\" \"$f\"\ndone\necho \"[rename] applied $SKY_NAME -> $SKY_NEW_NAME\""
§§

※※
Step 4 — verify. Lints the renamed file (catches a name<->filename mismatch) and
warns about any leftover `sky run <old>` references for manual cleanup.
※※

§verify§
depends_on = ["apply"]
bash = "set -e\nNEW=\"$SKY_DIR/$SKY_NEW_NAME.sky\"\nsky lint \"$NEW\"\nleft=$(grep -rl \"sky run $SKY_NAME\" \"$SKY_DIR\" 2>/dev/null || true)\nif [ -n \"$left\" ]; then echo \"[rename] WARNING leftover 'sky run $SKY_NAME' refs in:\"; echo \"$left\" | sed 's/^/    /'; fi\necho \"[rename] done -> $NEW\""
§§
